Not only his much-parodied vocal and presentation style, but the attitudes, the limited horizons it brings back to mind. Anyone under the age of 40 could only look on and scratch their heads. Could Britain really have been so dull, so limited back then? Well, yes, actually. And anyone who ever doubted the power of the goggle box in the corner of the living room to change attitudes, broaden horizons, even engender envy need only watch Whicker to see the seeds of our own more knowing, celebrity obsessed, mass-travelling, cosmetically enhanced era being sown right before their eyes. Whicker may only have been holding a mirror up to the wider world, and to the inevitably more sophisticated future. But what a hugely influential mirror it was.
